commitResults.messageTitle: Replaced Duke with Slipstream, and allowed it to repeat the inputs I give it
Changed Slipstream's function from responding to what I say to adding tasks to a list
Added a Task class to keep track of tasks, and allowed Slipstream to mark and unmark different tasks
Level-4, using different classes to manage different types of tasks. Also included an automated text UI tester
Added various exception handling using my custom class SlipstreamException. And, added a delete function for the bot. Tested using runtest and I think it works okay?

commitResults.messageBody:
Changes made:
* Included a new constructor for an already done task (using boolean isDone)
* Included a new String conversion for saved files
* Made Task an abstract class

FileSaving is a class that assists with:
* Saving tasks into a filepath
* Loading tasks from a filepath
* Reading tasks from a text file by converting from String in the text file to relevant Task type

Changes made:
* Fixed the indentation with switch cases
* Created a FileSaving object and used it to load and save tasks in relevant commands
* Added a "clear" command for users to clear all tasks since deleting one by one may take too long

Something went wrong with my merging and I thought reverting the commit would undo the merge,
but it didn't help. So I'm redoing the commit:

Changes made:
* Fixed the indentation with switch cases
* Created a FileSaving object and used it to load and save tasks in relevant commands
* Added a "clear" command for users to clear all tasks since deleting one by one may take too long

Added a specific format for deadlines to follow
* A written format in yyyy-mm-dd will be reformatted to MMM dd yyyyy when listed
* A SlipstreamException is thrown if the format is written wrongly

* SlipstreamException is now thrown in multiple methods when the date is written in the wrong format
--> Prevents a Deadline object from still being created

Modified the OOP of the code to make things more efficient:
* Renamed my initial FileSaving class to Storage as stated in the MoreOOP requirements
* Did use Github Copilot to autocomplete subsequent lines of switch cases in Parser and Ui messages to speed up codewriting

Organised Slipstream into a main slipstream package with subpackages for:
* Ui
* Task
* Parser
* Storage

Changes made with gradle:
* Many style changes using checkstyle
* Accidentally moved on to using JUnit before branching, so test classes are made

commitResults.messageTitle: Add SlipstreamTest and DeadlineTest for command validation
commitResults.messageBody:
Slipstream currently lacks automated tests for handling valid and invalid user commands, including task creation and deadline formatting.
Without these tests, errors may go unnoticed, and regressions may occur.

Let's add,
* SlipstreamTest to verify valid and invalid commands, ensuring proper error handling.
* DeadlineTest to test correct and incorrect deadline formats, catching parsing issues early.
Define archiveFileName as "slipstream.jar" to standardize output naming

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaDoc comments to Ui class
commitResults.messageBody:
Added JavaDoc comments to all methods in the all classes to improve code readability and maintainability.
Each method now includes a description, parameter details, and return values where applicable.

The project was already mostly compliant with the coding standard due to earlier changes. No major modifications were needed.
This commit removes unused files to maintain a clean codebase.
